{
  "kind": "browser-inspect",
  "red_failure_evidence": "On the real device the terminal showed only the last screen and swipes did nothing. Inspected: .xterm/.xterm-screen had pointer-events:auto, so xterm's touchmove handler received the gesture and preventDefault'd it to scroll its (disabled, overflow:visible/width:0) viewport, cancelling native scroll of .term-viewport. Headless used programmatic scrollTop so it masked this.",
  "green_evidence": "After: .term-viewport .xterm computed pointer-events=none, so touch falls through to .term-viewport (native scroll). Verified the container still scrolls (115->0), the Keys button still opens and the d-pad Down still sends <down>, and the reply flow is unaffected (buttons live outside .xterm). Pending real-device touch confirmation."
}
